<HEADLINE> Nepali Council of Ministers Portfolios Changed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra has, on
the recommendation of Prime Minister G.P. Koirala, made the
following changes in the allocation of portfolios in the Council
of Ministers constituted with the prime minister as the chairman.
</P>
<P>
According to a notice issued Tuesday by the principal
secretariat of the Royal Palace, the changes are as follows:
</P>
<P>
Girija Prasad Koirala -- Prime Minister; Minister for Royal
Palace Affairs; Minister for Women, Children and Social Welfare;
Minister for Defense, Minister for Labor and Transport Management;
Minister for General Administration;
</P>
<P>
Khum Bahadur Khadka -- Minister for Water Resources; Minister
for Physical Planning and Works;
</P>
<P>
Mahantha Thakur -- Minister for Law and Justice; Minister for
Parliamentary Affairs;
</P>
<P>
Ramkrishna Tamarakar -- Minister for Industry, Commerce and
Supplies;
</P>
<P>
Tarini Datta Chataut -- Minister for Culture; Minister for
Tourism and Civil Aviation;
</P>
<P>
Amod Prasad Upadhyaya -- Minister for Education and Sports;
</P>
<P>
Baldev Sharma Majgaiya -- Minister of State for Agriculture and
Cooperatives;
</P>
<P>
Kamala Panta -- Minister of State for Women, Children and
Social Welfare;
</P>
<P>
Narendra Bikram Nembang -- Minister of State for Industry,
Commerce and Supplies;
</P>
<P>
Dilendra Prasad Badu -- Minister of State for Education and
Sports;
</P>
<P>
Surendra Hamal -- Minister of State for Labor and Transport
Management.
</P>
<P>
The portfolios of other ministers are maintained as they are,
the notice said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
