<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Russia to Strengthen Strategic Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The presidents of Ukraine and Russia
met on Tuesday and expressed the will to strengthen strategic
partnership.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma said he was "deeply satisfied
" with the talks, adding that Vladimir Putin's visit laid a good
foundation for the development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
"Despite a series of problems in the Russian-Ukrainian
relations ... the strategic partnership between us will allow an
effective bilateral cooperation in political and economic fields,"
Kuchma said.
</P>
<P>
Putin, on the last leg of his three-nation tour which has taken
him to Britain and Belarus, was accompanied by Russia's foreign
and defense ministers and other top officials.
</P>
<P>
He described his talks with Kuchma as pragmatic, adding the two
countries should enhance cooperation in fields of economy,
security, culture and humanitarian aid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Economy Shows Signs of Improvement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China economy showed signs of an
upturn in the first quarter, and the growth of gross domestic
product (GDP) this year is expected to surpass that of last year,
an official of the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) said here
today.
</P>
<P>
NBS spokesman Liu Chengxiang told a press conference sponsored
by the Information Office of the State Council that four factors
will play an important role in promoting the economic growth,
including active fiscal policy, increasing export, fast
development of high-tech industries, and growing confidence among
both consumers and entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
China retained an economic growth rate of 8.1 percent in the
first quarter this year.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that since the economy has shown signs of improvement
because the first quarter figure was even better than the
relatively high growth rate in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In January-March, the country's fixed asset investment surged 8.
5 percent over the first quarter of last year. Meanwhile, exports
jumped 39.1 percent, the consumer price index (CPI) edged up 0.1
percent and retail sales soared 10.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Over the first two months of the year, the index of economic
efficiency of industrial enterprises improved by 15.6 points to 95.
83 points.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that this year's economic growth rate will be a little
higher than in 1999 given that all the fiscal policies are
properly implemented. China registered an economic growth of 7.1
percent last year. However, Liu said that inadequate consumption
demand remains as a major headache for the economy.
</P>
<P>
NBS predicts that the consumer price index (CPI) will break
free from a stand still and grow a moderate pace this year.
</P>
<P>
On the one hand, increasing government subsidies for lower-
income groups and prolonged holidays will continue to boost
consumerism. On the other hand, poor investment among non-
government sectors and recovering exports will weigh down
consumption demands.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that the Chinese government will continue to implement
active fiscal policies, stimulate demand, accelerate technological
advance and economic restructuring this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
