<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinian Students Hold Sit-in in Front of U.N. Office in Damascus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian students of
Damascus University held a silent sit-in in front of the United
Nations office here on Wednesday on the occasion of the "
Palestinian Captive Day."
</P>
<P>
The sit-in was called by the Palestinian Student Federation
(PSF) and the Committee on Defense of Palestinian Detainees in
Israeli Jails (CDPD).
</P>
<P>
The protesters handed over two memos, from the PSF and CDPD to
U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan, to the residing representative
of the U.N. Development Program in Damascus Tawfiq Bin Emara.
</P>
<P>
The two memos condemned the "atrocious and inhumane" treatment
practised by the Israeli occupation authorities against Palestinian
detainees.
</P>
<P>
The detainees are subject to various forms of physical and
psychological torture and deprived of medical care, the memos said,
noting that the intimidation was aimed at undermining the religious
and national values of the detainees.
</P>
<P>
Israel holds 3,272 Arabs in its prisons, including 90
administrative detainees and six female prisoners. More than 320
detainees are sick, including 36 cases of blindness and renal
failure that were caused by torture, according to the memos.
</P>
<P>
The protesters urged the United Nations and the international
community to step in immediately to stop the Israeli atrocities and
facilitate the release of the Palestinian detainees according to
relevant U.N. Security Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
The protesters distributed a statement addressing the
international public opinion on the Israeli inhumane practices
against the Palestinian and Arab detainees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
