<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Anti-Iran Resolution on Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman
Hamid Reza Asefi on Wednesday lashed out at a United Nations
resolution passed recently criticizing the human rights situation
in Iran.
</P>
<P>
The politically motivated resolution fell short of reflecting
the realities in Iran's dynamic society, and it is only a
repetition of the allegations already made against the country,
Asefi said.
</P>
<P>
He condemned the sponsors of the anti-Iran resolution, accusing
them of exploiting political and economic leverages to draw votes
against Tehran, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Iran has an agenda to honor human rights and guarantee the
fundamental freedoms of the people in line with religious beliefs,
the Islamic values and the stipulations of the constitution, Asefi
said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Iran has reinforced the rule of law, democracy and
the humanitarian values in the country.
</P>
<P>
He also thanked countries voting against the anti-Iran
resolution which was issued by the U.N. Human Rights Commission in
Geneva. 
</P>
