<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Delivers Speech in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang
Zemin delivered a speech here on Wednesday on the Sino-Turkish
relations, the international situation, domestic affairs and other
issues at a banquet held in his honour by his Turkish counterpart
Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
On the Sino-Turkish relations, Jiang said the friendship between
the two peoples dates back to ancient times, with the evidence of
the world-known "Silk Road" linking China and the Asia Minor
peninsular more than 2000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Through this ancient road, he added, the forefathers of the two
peoples made extensive exchanges and promoted, together with other
nations, trade and the communication of civilizations of the East
and West.
</P>
<P>
The exquisite porcelain which was made in various dynasties in
ancient China and is now in store in the Topkapi Palace in Istanbul
bear vivid testimony to the lasting friendship between the two
peoples, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also hailed the remarkable achievements made by the
Turkish people, as reflected in continuous social advancement and
rapid economic development, adding Turkey has become a country that
attracts the attention of the world community.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said it is of vital importance for China
and Turkey, located respectively at the east and west ends of the
Asian continent, to develop a new relationship of cooperation and
partnership.
</P>
<P>
Touching upon the world affairs, Jiang said there is a general
trend of tension-easing in the international situation, but the
world is far from being tranquil.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that maintaining the world peace and promoting
common development is the theme of the present time and the
universal aspiration of the world people.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that on one hand, a lasting international peaceful
environment is necessary for China, which is now pursuing reforms
and opening up to the outside world and pushing forward the
modernization drive, on the other hand, the world peace and
development also necessitate the stability and development in
China.
</P>
<P>
China, which follows the foreign policy of peace and
independence, is a major force in maintaining the world peace and
stability, the Chinese president said.
</P>
<P>
On domestic affairs, Jiang said the 56 nationalities in China
have forged solid links in which they learn from each other, depend
on each other, help each other and promote the benefits of each
other.
</P>
<P>
Since the ancient times, Jiang said, the different nationalities
in China, who have displayed an immense cohesion and a longstanding
tradition of patriotism, have been of one heart in founding and
building their country.
</P>
<P>
He said the cultures and traditions of minorities have been held
on respect and protection and each minority can keep and develop
its own culture.
</P>
<P>
Recently, he said, China has embarked on a strategic mission of
developing the west region of the country, partly in a bid to
accelerate the economic, social and cultural development in the
minorities areas there.
</P>
<P>
He said that China, where many religions such as Taoism,
Buddhism, Islam and Christianity are in existence, has adopted the
policy of respecting and protecting the freedom of religious
beliefs, followed the principle of separating religion from
political power and education.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that the country protects normal religious
activities and the legitimate rights of religious groups, with the
different religions sharing equal status and in peaceful co-
existence, and religious believers and non-believers respecting
each other and living in unity and harmony.
</P>
<P>
As there are nearly 200 countries and regions, more than 2,500
nationalities as well as many religions in the world, Jiang said,
proper handling of the ethnic and religious issues is of vital
significance to maintaining world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that as the world is colorful, the varieties and
disparities among different nationalities, the religions and the
civilizations should be respected.
</P>
<P>
In dealing with their mutual relations, he said that tolerance,
communication, dialog and co-existence should be advocated while
discrimination, repellence, confrontation and conflicts be opposed.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of mutual respect, equality and the principle of
seeking common ground while reserving differences, the positive
sides of all the civilizations should be given full play to boost
incessant development of the human society and achieve the common
progress of all countries and peoples on earth.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that throughout the ages, the mutual discrimination,
repellence, confrontation and conflicts among the countries and
peoples with different religious beliefs and ethnics, not only
inflict damages and disasters on the related countries and peoples,
but also undermine the stability, tranquility and development in
many regions and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The international community should bear in mind these lessons,
he stressed, saying the overweening arrogance, and the agitation of
national split and hatred among different ethnics go against the
historical trend and harm the lofty cause of peace and development
in the world.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also attached importance to adhering to and reinforcing
the common understanding between China and Turkey on safeguarding
each other's sovereignty, territorial integrity and ethnic unity.
</P>
<P>
In the 20th century, both China and Turkey experienced
remarkable changes. Since the founding of the People's Republic of
China and the Republic of Turkey, the two peoples, in line with the
conditions of their own countries, have gone all out and worked
hard to score remarkable achievements, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said, China's economy has been growing at an annual
average of 7.7 percent for the past 50 years while Turkey's
comprehensive national strength has ranked the 16th in the world.
</P>
<P>
This, he added, testifies that the peoples of ancient nations
certainly can make continuous progress in their development, so
long as they give active play to their profound cultural
accumulation and tradition of braveness and hard-working, and
absorb the latest achievements in the scientific and cultural
fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
