<HEADLINE> Jiang's Turkey Visit a Historic One: Demirel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
said here Wednesday that the ongoing visit to Turkey by Chinese
President Jiang Zemin has not only brought the traditional
friendship of the Chinese people to the country, but furthered the
bilateral friendly ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a banquet he hosted in honour of the Chinese
president, Demirel called the visit a "historic" one which will
guarantee the prospect of the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is looking forward to pushing the Turkey-China relations
to a new height, Demirel said.
</P>
<P>
He cited the joint communique signed between the two countries
earlier in the day as a document to push the bilateral ties to the
level of closer partnership.
</P>
<P>
The communique demonstrated the willingness of the two sides to
consolidate the bilateral relations, he added.
</P>
<P>
Turkey hopes that China will join the World Trade Organization
at an earlier date because China's WTO admission will create new
opportunities for the Turkey-China economic cooperation and trade,
the president said.
</P>
<P>
He continued that besides governmental departments, the private
businesses of the two countries will take the opportunity to make
contributions to the balanced development of two-way trade.
</P>
<P>
Demirel expressed his appreciation for the great progress China
has made in its economic development in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish people hope that China will fulfill the
reunification cause under the guidance of the "One Country, Two
Systems" policy, he noted.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang arrived here Tuesday for a state visit as the
guest of Demirel. Turkey is the third leg of his five-nation visit,
which had brought him to Israel and Palestine, and will take him to
Greece and South Africa. 
</P>
