<HEADLINE> Peruvian Entrepreneurs Support Fujimori's Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The third term of President
Fujimori will guarantee Peru's economic stability, said the 38
principal companies of the country, in a survey presented on
Wednesday by the financial consultary "Maximixe."
</P>
<P>
In this survey, Fujimori got 80 percent of the preferences of
Peruvian entrepreneurs, who consider that the presidential
opponent, Alejandro Toledo, lacks a more solid economic proposal.
</P>
<P>
As for the financial system agents' expectations, the survey
results reveal that there are no fears of social turmoil in case
Fujimori is reelected.
</P>
<P>
According to the consultants, Toledo's image has been affected
by his populist promises ant the changes in his positions.
</P>
<P>
Among Toledo's unpracticable proposals, according with the
survey, are the creation of 400,000 jobs during the first three
months of his term, activating production with a tax reduction and
an increase in public sector's expenditure.
</P>
<P>
Fujimori and Toledo will dispute the presidential post in a
second electoral round, scheduled by the second week of June,
because none of them got a majority of votes during the first
round on April 9.  
</P>
