<HEADLINE> Rwanda to Close Illegal Religious Sects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- All religious sects in Rwanda are
to be closed because of their illegal operation, Rwanda News
Agency quoted official sources as saying on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Cabinet members stressed in their extraordinary session the
need to close religious sects without legal requirements and those
that discourage their followers from work.
</P>
<P>
"All religious sects which do not have registration
certificates should be closed down, particularly sects that
propagate false teachings to their followers", Christopher
Bazivamo, the Prefect of Gitarama prefecture in central Rwanda,
disclosed during a meeting with religious leaders.
</P>
<P>
The government move came in the wake of the death of hundreds
of doomsday cult members in neighboring Uganda.
</P>
<P>
About 10 members of a new religious cult that believes in
worshipping God only, avoiding doing any other activity and
convinced that the end of the world was imminent were arrested in
Byumba following illegal worshipping practices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
