was attended by some 125 arms and ammunitions companies from 40
countries.
</P>
<P>
The event is expected to open a window for Jordan on the latest
developments of equipments and technologies concerning special
forces operations, and it would be also a venue for potential
cooperations between participants, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
On display are heavy equipments like advanced bombers, armed
helicopters, tanks and armored vehicles as well as guns, anti-riot
equipments, bullet-proof vests and other logistical materials and
equipments.
</P>
<P>
Shelton also met with his Jordanian counterpart Muhammad Yousef
Malkawi on Wednesday for talks on bilateral defence and military
cooperation and issues of mutual interest, Petra said.
</P>
<P>
Shelton's visit to the kingdom is also within the framework of
the high-level military contacts between Jordan and the U.S., which
takes the kingdom as an important ally in the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. government provided some 300 million U.S. dollars in
various military and economic aid packages to the kingdom in 1999.
