<HEADLINE> China Calls for Concerted Efforts in Protecting Civilians in Armed Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The issue of protecting
civilians in armed conflict involves political, peace-keeping,
humanitarian, disarmament, legal and many other dimensions and it
needs the concerted efforts by the whole international community
as well as the United Nations, China stressed here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Security Council's open debate on the
protection of civilians in armed conflict, Chinese Permanent
Representative to the United Nations, Wang Yingfan, said in
considering the issue, the Security Council should have a clear
division of work and enhance coordination and cooperation with
other bodies.
</P>
<P>
Wang said the 40 recommendations in the U.N.Secretary-General'
s previous report were not put forward for the Security Council
only, and many of them require the General Assembly, the Economic
and Social Council, the Office of the U.N. High Commissioner for
Refugees and other relevant bodies to review and handle.
</P>
<P>
"In our view, all agencies within the U.N. system should have
a clear description and division of work and duty. The Security
Council can review and handle this issue within its own mandate
and by doing so support and cooperate with efforts in this regard
by other relevant agencies," the Ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
"This is the only way that different departments of U.N. can
work in harmony and mutual-enhancement, and the U.N. system as a
whole can play its role more effectively," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0037 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China: Security Council Should Seek to Eradicate Causes of Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 19(Xinhua) -- The United Nations Security
Council should, apart from addressing the issue of protection of
civilians in armed conflict at hand, seek to eradicate the causes
of armed conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Security Council's open debate on protecting
civilians in armed conflict, Chinese Permanent Representative to
the United Nations, Wang Yingfan, said with its primary
responsibility of the maintenance of international peace and
security, the Security Council should draw upon both successes and
failures in the past so as to perform its duties in a more
effective manner, with a view to creating a favorable
international environment of peace for all regions and countries.
</P>
<P>
"The Council should focus its efforts to find solutions of the
armed conflicts. Only by creating an overall favorable and
peaceful environment and defusing at an early date the specific
conflicts and disputes, can the effective protection of civilians
be truly realized,' the Ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
"At the same time, we believe that the international community
and relevant U.N. bodies should take further steps to eradicate
the root causes of the conflicts by helping relevant countries to
eliminate poverty, develop economy, promote national
reconciliation and safeguard domestic stability," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Only by these means can a fundamental solution be reached to
the issue of protection of civilians in armed conflict, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
