<HEADLINE> Britain to Help S. Africa Improve Public Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Britain agreed to provide
South Africa with assistance worth 30 million rand (about five
million U.S. dollars) to improve the performance and efficiency of
its public service, a government department said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
