direct a greater proportion of its government spending to
development objectives and increase public participation in
policy-making," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the assistance, Fraser-Moleketi said: "It will make
an important contribution to South Africa's aim of creating a
people-centred and people-driven public service, characterized by
equity, equality, timeousness and a strong code of ethics."
</P>
<P>
Short said: "The challenge now is to make sure that the new
public service works for everyone in South Africa. The UK is
committed to further supporting the efforts of the South African
government to reduce poverty and inequality, through more
effective delivery of public services to all." 
