<HEADLINE> OAU Urged to Consult African States on Pan African Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Parliamentary Forum of
the Southern Africa Development Community (SADC) on Wednesday
urged the Organization of African Unity (OAU) not to take any
further decisions on a proposed Pan African Parliament until all
African parliaments have been consulted.
</P>
<P>
Forum chairwoman, South African National Assembly Speaker Frene
Ginwala, said a survey of African countries had shown that most of
their parliaments were not consulted on the issue.
</P>
<P>
She told a meeting of the forum's plenary in Cape Town that a
meeting, however, was underway at OAU headquarters in Addis Ababa
to establish a draft protocol for a Pan African Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The forum had thus written to the OAU, asking it not to
finalize the matter until it had heard from all African
parliaments, Ginwala said.
</P>
<P>
Just before the forum adjourned on Wednesday afternoon, Ginwala
informed the 14 SADC countries' delegations attending the meeting
that a response was awaited from the OAU, which would be
circulated among SADC member states.
</P>
<P>
A Malawian delegate said that depending on the reply, a debate
could be held at the next forum meeting later this year, according
to the South African Press Association.
</P>
<P>
The proposal on establishing the Pan African Parliament was
raised at an OAU meeting last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
