<HEADLINE> Thai Int'l Airport Replaced by 2004 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The newly-developed Nong Ngoo Hao
Airport will be Thailand's sole international airport, replacing
the Don Muang Airport, by 2004, the official Thai News Agency
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It said the new international airport would have the potential
to fully serve international passengers after four years.
</P>
<P>
The Nong Ngoo Hao Airport, located in Bangkok suburban province
of Samut Prakarn, could serve 30 million passengers in 2004, and
its capacity would be expanded to serve 50 million passengers by
2006,according to the report.
</P>
<P>
It said the airport could serve up to 70 million passengers
when its development was completed.
</P>
<P>
Foreign arrivals would also use the Nong Ngoo Hao Airport as
their sole base to fly to other Thai provincial airports in Chiang
Rai,Chiang Mai, Phuket or Had Yai, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It also said that the Don Muang Airport would then be
transformed to be an industrial estate or a training center for
pilots.
</P>
<P>
In the initial stage, the Don Muang Airport might be used as a
domestic airport before all passengers would use the Nong Ngoo Hao
Airport as their sole air-journey base, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
