<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Private Entrepreneurs Urged to Increase Export Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Commerce Minister Abdul Jalil
Wednesday called on the private sector entrepreneurs to utilize
the export opportunities in the globalized trade system through
increasing export base.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh has to overcome its dependency on limited items of
export and destinations like the American and European markets to
face the challenges of globalization of trade, he said while
addressing at the 23rd meeting of the Export Promotion Council (
EPC) at a hotel here.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the country's five-year export policy, the
minister said the government is always acting as facilitator for
promoting export. The EPC meeting discussed the present export
situation and formulated future strategy for enhancing export
volume, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, goods worth 2,695.46 million U.S.
dollars exported during July 1999 to February 2000 which is 332.40
million dollars more than the corresponding period of the previous
fiscal year. The export target is fixed at 5,738 million dollars
with a growth rate of 9.88 percent in the current fiscal year.
</P>
</TEXT>
