<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Contribute to IFAD </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will contribute
about 250,000 U.S. dollars to the fifth replenishment of the
International Fund for Agricultural Development (IFAD).
</P>
<P>
A motion by the Finance Ministry for the contribution was
passed in the Dewan Rakyat (House of Representatives) here
Wednesday, Bernama news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
IFAD, set up under the auspices of the United Nations in 1987,
provides assistance to developing countries in the agriculture
field and the major beneficiaries of IFAD are African countries,
according to Deputy Finance Minister Shafie Mohamed Salleh.
</P>
<P>
He said in Parliament that Malaysia has so far contributed 500,
000 U.S. dollars to IFAD and the country has yet to reap benefits
from contributing to IFAD. 
</P>
</TEXT>
