<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Children Admit Causing Belgian Train Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Three children, 8, 9 and 13
years of age, have confessed to placing a concrete block on train
tracks on the Charleroi-Namur line, causing a head-on train
collision Tuesday in which the driver of one train was killed.
</P>
<P>
Local media reported Wednesday that the concrete block was laid
on a crucial switch and caused one train to derail. An oncoming
train crashed into it at high speed. Three people were seriously
injured and some 20 others suffered light injuries.
</P>
<P>
Traffic was temporarily suspended on the southern Belgian line,
which is also the route between Paris and Cologne.
</P>
<P>
Some Belgium rail workers stopped work Wednesday morning to
express condolences to their dead colleague.
</P>
<P>
Wreckage of one train has already been towed away. Clearance
work will be concluded by Thursday, according to railway
authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
