<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks gained 148.88
points, or 0.97 percent to close at 15,427.20 points Wednesday
after a second straight gain on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The turnover on the Hong Kong market Wednesday totaled 11.776
billion HK dollars (1.51 billion U.S.dollars), as against 12.586
billion HK dollars (1.6 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of the benchmark Hang Seng Index,
Finance, Utilities, and Commerce &AMP; Industry gained 1.76 percent, 1.
50 percent and 1.04 percent while Properties lost 0.77 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China Enterprises Index slid 0.81 percent, or 3.05
points, to 371.39 while the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corp Index
fell 1.57 percent, or 19.69 points, to close at 1,231.12 points.
</P>
<P>
The HSI opened 280.20 points, or 1.83 percent, higher at 15,558.
52 points in the morning and closed the morning session at 15,584.
28 points, up 305.96 points, or 2.00 percent. 
</P>
