<HEADLINE> Housing Website Joins China.com </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese website catering to
people's housing needs signed an agreement with www.china.com to
become partners.
</P>
<P>
The www.anjia.com website offers information and consultation
on where to buy or rent houses, how to design and furnish homes,
and as well as reviews on daily consumer items.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the anjia website will become the "
housing channel" for China.com and the Chinese version of www.aol.
com.
</P>
<P>
Xu Yiqun, technology supervisor of China.com, said that the
partnership will bring about more registered users for the China.
com, with more Chinese buying houses.
</P>
<P>
Since 1997, housing sales in China's major cities has risen by
an annual rate of 50 percent.  
