<HEADLINE> China Digital Library Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China Digital Library Corp. Ltd.
(CDLC) has launched the China Digital Library Project.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony at the National Library of China Tuesday, Xu
Jialu, vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress, and Ai Qingchun, vice-minister of culture
attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The CDLC will set up high-quality multimedia repositories,
provide digital information services and develop e-commerce.
</P>
<P>
With a registered capital of 20 million yuan (2.4 million U.S.
dollars), the corporation is aiming to be listed on the stock
exchange and collect funds from public and private sources, Zhou
Heping, the corporation general manager, said.
</P>
<P>
The China Ditigal-library Net launched by the corporation was
also officially opened Tuesday. 
