<HEADLINE> Jiang, Ecevit Agree to Advance Bilateral Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here Wednesday that the Sino-Turkish relations have
advanced smoothly since they established diplomatic ties in 1971,
thanks to the joint efforts of the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The two countries should further their cooperation in various
fields to promote bilateral relations in an all-round way, Jiang
said at a luncheon hosted by Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit
in his honor.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he believes his ongoing visit will help push forward
the bilateral relations. He expressed thanks for the hospitality of
the Turkish government and people, and conveyed Chinese Premier Zhu
Rongji's regards to Ecevit.
</P>
<P>
Jiang welcomed Turkish businessmen to participate in the great
development of China's western region, rich in natural resources
but lack in industrial development.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit extended his welcome to Jiang, and expressed his
appreciation for China's assistance to Turkey when the country was
hit by devastating earthquakes last year.
</P>
<P>
He said Turkish government values its ties with China and is
willing to develop friendship with the great country.
</P>
<P>
Turkey would like to strengthen cooperation with China in the
fields of trade, investment, culture and tourism, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived in Turkey Tuesday for a state visit at the
invitation of Turkish President Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is the third leg of Jiang's five-nation visit, which will
also take him to Greece and South Africa. He had visited Israel and
Palestine, and held a meeting with President Hosni Mubarak in
Egypt's Mediterranean port city of Alexandria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Turkey Sign Joint Communique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China and Turkey signed a joint
communique here Wednesday, expressing their common determination to
further develop the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The joint communique was signed by visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin and his Turkish counterpart Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
The two countries decided to forge closer ties of partnership on
the basis of mutual respect, trust and benefit, as well as equality
and common development, according to the document.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president arrived here Tuesday for a state visit to
Turkey at the invitation of Demirel. Jiang held talks with Demirel,
and met with Speaker of Turkey's Grand National Assembly Yildirim
Akbulut and Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit on separate occasions.
</P>
<P>
In a friendly and constructive atmosphere, the leaders of the
two countries exchanged views on the bilateral relations, and
international and regional issues with common concern, and reached
consensus on a variety of topics, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the two countries signed a summary of the 13th
meeting of the Sino-Turkish joint committee of economy and trade,
and a framework agreement on the bilateral cooperation in the
energy field.
</P>
<P>
In the communique, Jiang and Demirel expressed their
satisfaction with the development of bilateral ties since the two
countries established diplomatic relations 29 years ago, which they
said conforms to the common aspiration and the fundamental interest
of the peoples of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have taken notice of the fact that promoting peace
and development, adhering to the commonly-accepted principles and
safeguarding the security of all countries have become the basic
requirements of the modern international community, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
While expressing their determination to pushing forward the
friendly bilateral relations, the two sides reiterated their
respect for human rights.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that bilateral relations will continue to be
guided by the well-acknowledged international norms such as mutual
respect for independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity,
non-aggression, non-interference in each other's internal affairs,
equality and mutual benefit as well as peaceful co-existence.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish government reaffirmed its commitment to the "One
China" policy and recognition that the government of the People's
Republic of China is the sole, legitimate government of China.
</P>
<P>
The two sides pledged to maintain exchanges and contacts at
various levels to consolidate the existing friendly cooperation,
and to elevate the relationship in the new century.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will continue their top-level political
consultation through the mechanism enshrined in the memorandum of
understanding signed between their foreign ministries on November
13, 1997 as an effort to advance and deepen the overall relations.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the two countries also treasure the relationship
between China's National People's Congress and Turkey's Grand
National Assembly, and will expand parliamentary exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The two countries saw great potential and good prospect for
bilateral trade, and agreed that the growth of economic and trade
ties is not only mutually beneficial, but also conducive to their
overall cooperation and understanding, the communique stated.
</P>
<P>
China and Turkey will work hard to expand business and economic
cooperation, pursue constant growth of trade in a balanced and
diversified manner, explore new measures and channels to cement
economic and technological cooperation, encourage mutual
investments, and take neccessary measures to enhance their share in
each other's markets, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the two countries will also encourage the exchanges
in the fields of economy, science and technology and environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
To accomplish these objectives, the two countries will hold
regular meetings of their joint economic committee to ensure its
decisions implemented. Furthermore, the two countries will also
support the Sino-Turkish association of entrepreneurs and encourage
the cooperation between business communities.
</P>
<P>
As two rapidly growing energy markets, the two countries will
further promote and support their joint study and cooperation in
the energy sectors, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
The two countries agreed that reinvigorating the ancient Silk
Road, which had played an important role in furthering the
friendship and exchanges of eastern and western civilizations, will
help promote the cooperation and friendship among countries along
the road.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also decided to intensify cooperation in tourism
and journalism, encourage the application of advanced technology in
people-to-people contacts, further exchanges in the fields of
culture, art, science, education and sports, as well as between
twin cities and provinces, support activities to protect historical
and cultural heritage, and promote contacts between local
governments.
</P>
<P>
To this end, the two sides agreed to fulfill the basic legal,
economic, financial and business works in accordance with their
respective international responsibilities, the document stipulated.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also pledged to offer as much convenience as
possible to the activities of each other's diplomatic, consular,
commercial and other official representative institutes, on the
basis of the principle of reciprocity.
</P>
<P>
They are of the opinion that profound changes are taking place
in the world, the trend of political multi-polarization and
economic globalization is moving forward, and there still exist
lots of elements that could lead to instability and crisis.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are willing to make new contributions to
peace, stability, trust, mutual understanding, and mutual and
multi-lateral cooperation in the world, said the document.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also hold that both China and Turkey are important
countries in the region, and share views on many regional and
international issues while committing themselves to safeguarding
peace in the region and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
They decided to maintain and promote their established political
consultation mechanism, and coordination and cooperation on
international affairs. The two countries will pay attention to the
international economic and financial issues to ensure a stable
environment for development.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the two governments reaffirmed to make effort to
advance the process of arms control and disarmament, and prevent
the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction and their means of
delivery, because they have noted that these efforts will be
conducive to safeguarding and strengthening the international
security.
</P>
<P>
The two countries affirmed their firm opposition to terrorism,
regardless of its form, cause and objective. The two sides will
further cooperate in combating terrorism, and join efforts in
cracking down on organized crimes, smuggling and other cross-border
criminal activities.
</P>
<P>
The two countries act in accordance with their own laws to ban
any illegal activity on their soil, including splittism and ultra-
religionism in all their forms.
</P>
<P>
In the communique, China and Turkey advocate peaceful settlement
of international conflicts, oppose the use, or threat of use, of
force in international relations, support the important role the
United Nations and the U.N. Security Council have been playing in
safeguarding world peace and security as well as in other fields.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also stressed the importance of abiding by the
objectives and principles of the U.N. Charter.
</P>
<P>
It is of great significance to maintain frequent contacts and
exchange of visits between leaders of the two countries, the
communique also stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0089 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Files Complaint Over Katyusha Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Israel on Wednesday filed a
complaint with the Grapes of Wrath Monitoring Committee (GWMC),
accusing Lebanese Hezbollah guerrillas for their Katyusha attacks
against Israel's northern civilian targets.
</P>
<P>
Israeli military said that several long-range 122-millimeter
Katyusha rockets fired by Hezbollah guerrillas hit western Galilee,
northern Israel, Tuesday afternoon. One of them hit the road at the
entrance to a settlement, which damaged an electricity transformer
and caused a blackout in the region for several hours.
</P>
<P>
Following the attack, the Israel Defense Forces (IDF) in the
north was ordered to be on alert, as the Israeli military said that
the Katyusha attack against the Israeli civilians was deliberate
and categorized it as "very grave."
</P>
<P>
Israel has in the compliant asked the GWMC to investigate the
incident and warned that if Hezbollah guerrillas fire more Katyusha
rockets against northern Israel, Israel will respond drastically,
Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The GWMC, a five-nation group, was set up to supervise the
understandings reached at the end of the Operation Grapes of Wrath
in April 1996.
</P>
<P>
Israel Air Force fighter jets struck several Hezbollah targets
early Wednesday morning in south Lebanon in an apparent move to
retaliate for the Tuesday Katyusha attacks.
</P>
<P>
But no immediate reports of casualties among the Lebanese were
reported so far.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's Katyusha attacks came at the peak of a day of heavy
skirmishing in southern Lebanon that left one Syrian construction
worker dead and five people injured, including two IDF soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli military said the long-range 122-millimeter caliber
Katyusha model fired by Hezbollah on Tuesday has not been in use
for some time.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, or Party of God, backed by Iran and Syria, is one of
the Lebanese resistance forces that have been fighting against the
Israeli occupation of south Lebanon since 1978. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
