<HEADLINE> Nationwide River Protection Campaign in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A nation wide campaign to clean
China's major rivers will be carried out to coincide with "Earth
Day from 22-30 of April.
</P>
<P>
The project to protect China's rivers was initiated early last
year by the Central Committee of the Communist Youth League,
Ministry of Water Resources, National Greening Committee, State
Forestry Administration and the China Youth Development Foundation.
</P>
<P>
Young volunteers in 108 cities along ten major rivers including
the Yellow River, the Yangtze River, the Songhuajiang River and
the Huaihe River will participate in the project, according to the
Central Committee of the Communist Youth League.
</P>
<P>
They will take floating litter out of rivers, place sorted
dustbins and monitor ecological conditions along the rivers.
</P>
<P>
Managers from factories located along these rivers will also
take part in the clean up campaign.  
</P>
