of principles of mutual respect, mutual trust and non-interference
in each other's internal affairs;
</P>
<P>
-- pursuing the common and mutually beneficial economic
development for the interests of the peoples of the two countries;
</P>
<P>
-- expanding exchanges in the fields of culture, education,
science and technology in order to enhance people-to-people
understanding and friendship;
</P>
<P>
-- making commitment to cracking down on all forms of
international terrorism, ethnic splittism and ultra-religionism;
</P>
<P>
-- making consultations and coordinating stance on international
affairs to safeguard the regional and international peace and
stability.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang arrived in Turkey Tuesday for a state visit at
the invitation of Demirel.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is the third leg of Jiang's five-nation tour, which has
taken him to Israel and Palestine, and will take him to Greece and
South Africa. He has also conferred with Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak in the Alexandria city of Egypt. 
