the latest developments of the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Arafat arrived here Tuesday night for talks with Mubarak before
flying to Washington to discuss with U.S. President Bill Clinton on
Thursday ways of pushing forward the Palestinian-Israeli
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
"It is important to wait for the result of the Arafat-Clinton
meeting before talking about progress or lack of progress on the
Palestinian track," Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa told
reporters after Mubarak met with Arafat.
</P>
