progress in the peace march,'' Moussa said.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians and Israel are negotiating for a final
settlement of the thorniest issues, including borders, water
resources, the fate of Jerusalem, refugees and Jewish settlements,
in their final-status talks. The two sides have agreed to sign a
permanent peace agreement on the issues in September.
</P>
<P>
Arafat frequently visits Egypt to consult and coordinate stances
on the peace process with Mubarak, who, as president of the first
Arab country to sign a peace treaty with Israel, plays an active
role in mediating between the Palestinians and Israel. 
