<HEADLINE> Bank of Greece Cuts Key Intervention Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Greece, the country's
central bank, Wednesday reduced its key intervention rates by
between 0.50 and 0.75 basis points.
</P>
<P>
This is the fifth such reduction by the central bank in six
months.
</P>
<P>
The bank announced a 0.50-percentage point reduction in the
weekly intervention rate for two-week funds from 9.25 percent to 8.
75 percent.
</P>
<P>
