<HEADLINE> Turkish President Demirel Host Ceremony to Welcome Chinese President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKALA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
held a grand ceremony at the Presidential Palace Wednesday morning
to welcome Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Upon their arrival at the presidential Palace, President Jiang
and his wife Wang Yeping were warmly greeted by Demirel and his
wife Nazniye.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Demirel mounted to the reviewing stand amid a salvo
of 21 guns. The national anthems of China and Turkey were played.
Accompanied by Demirel, Jiang inspected a guard of honor greeting
them in Turkish "Merhaba Asker."
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Demirel said that Turkey attaches great
importance to the development of relations with the People's
Republic of China and Turkey and China have very long historic
contacts.
</P>
<P>
As two great civilized ancient nations on the east and west ends
of the Asian Continent, China and Turkey play a very significant
role in maintaining regional stability, balance and prosperity and
in developing world economy, Demirel said. So there is a bright
prospect of cooperation between the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Demirl expressed his confidence that President Jiang's state
visit will further accelerate the friendly relations of cooperation
between Turkey and China, and contribute to the establishment of a
brand-new partnership in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, President Jiang said that the friendship between
Chinese and Turkish peoples dates back to 2000 years ago, when
their ancestors began friendly contacts via the famous "Silk Road."
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of diplomatic relations in 1971, Sino-
Turkish friendly exchanges in various fields increased and
cooperative relationship progressed, Jiang stressed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that his visit to Turkey, which comes at the turn of
the century, aims to deepen mutual understanding, promote
friendship and advance cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The visit also aims to establish a new cooperative partnership
between the two countries in the new era, for the benefit of the
two countries and the two peoples, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I look forward to holding constructive and fruitful talks with
President Demirel and other Turkish leaders so as to make joint
efforts to achieve this goal," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President said that he was very pleased to pay a
state visit to Turkey, a renowned nation with ancient civilization,
and he had brought with him deep affections and good wishes from
the Chinese people to the friendly Turkish people.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was attended by Speaker of the Turkish Grand
National Assembly Yildirim Akbulut, Deputy Prime Minister and
Minister of Enegy and Natural Resources Cumhur Ersumer, Minister of
Transport Enis Oksuz, and Chinese Deputy Premier Qian Qichen and
State Councillor Wu Yi who are accompanying President Jiang on the
current visit.
</P>
<P>
Before the ceremony President Jiang laid a wreath at Anitkabir
and visited the Atarturk Museum.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang arrived in Ankara Tuesday afternoon for a state
visit to Turkey. Turkey is the third leg of Jiang's five-nation
state visit, which had already taken him to Israel and Palestine.
He also flew to Egypt's Mediterranean port city of Alexandria for a
meeting with President Hosni Mubarak. 
</P>
