<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Upper House of Parliament Ratifies START II </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Federation Council,
upper house of parliament, Wednesday ratified the Russian-U.S.
second-phase Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty (START II) by a vote
of 126 against 18 with six abstentions.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Russian State Duma, lower chamber of parliament,
passed the treaty on April 14 by 288 votes in favor with 131
against and four abstentions.
</P>
<P>
The treaty, signed by former Russian President Boris Yeltsin
and his American counterpart George Bush on January 3, 1993,
provides for the reduction before December 31, 2007 of the total
number of nuclear warheads carried by intercontinental ballistic
missiles, submarine-based ballistic missiles and heavy bombers to
3,000-3,500.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Senate ratified the treaty in January 1996.
</P>
<P>
Before coming into effect, the pact must be signed by Russian
President-elect Vladimir Putin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
