<HEADLINE> Liaoning Upgrades Small Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Northeast china's Liaoning
Province, one of China's major industrial bases, are making
efforts to promote the development of small- and medium-sized
enterprises as one of solutions to its problems in economic growth.
</P>
<P>
At present, the 400,000 small- and medium sized enterprises in
the province employ 8 million people, accounting for 40 percent of
the labor force engaged in various industries and services.
</P>
<P>
The added-value of the enterprises reached 129.9 billion yuan (
15.28 billion U.S. dollars) last year, accounting for 73 percent
of the industrial added-value in the province.
</P>
<P>
The taxes turned over by the small- and medium-sized
enterprises took up 31.6 percent of the total of the industrial
enterprises in Liaoning last year.
</P>
<P>
With a high proportion of large state-owned enterprises (SOEs),
Liaoning has a heavy task in the SOE reform and helping them
overcome difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Guoguang, governor of the province, said that Liaoning
has set a strategy to promote its economic growth by developing
small- and medium-sized enterprises, noting that the province will
focus on promoting a great batch of small and medium-sized
enterprises engaged in development of new and high technology and
export-oriented business.
</P>
<P>
This year the Finance Department of Liaoning Province invested
60 million yuan (7 million U.S. dollars) in the establishment of a
scientific and technological guarantee company to help small- and
medium-sized enterprises engage in technological innovation.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning is also formulating preferential policies for the
small- and medium-sized enterprises so as to broaden their
operation scope.  
</P>
</TEXT>
