<HEADLINE> Macao Sees More Trade Surplus in First Two Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The figure soared by 718.2 percent over that in the same period
last year, according to the figures released Wednesday by the
Statistics and Census Services of the Macao SAR government.
</P>
<P>
In the two months, the area's export and import volumes were 2.
58 billion patacas (322.5 million U.S. dollars) and 2.05 billion
patacas (256.25 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Textiles and garments remained the leading export items,
accounting for 80.7 percent of all exports in January and February.
</P>
<P>
On the whole, exports to the United States and the European
Union accounted for 42.8 percent and 36 percent respectively of
the total exports. And exports to China's inland areas and Hong
Kong represented 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
Most imports came from the Asian-Pacific region. China's inland
areas and Hong Kong supplied 54 percent of the total. Goods from
the United States and the European Union accounted for 15.1
percent.  
