<HEADLINE> Two Seeds Upset in Monte Carlo Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Sixth-seeded Thomas Enqvist and
seventh-seeded Tim Henman were upset in the second round matches
of the 2.95 million US dollars Monte Carlo Masters Series on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Swede Enqvist was defeated by former Wimbledon champion Richard
Krajicek 7-5, 6-1 while Briton Henman lost to Argentine qualifier
Juan Ignacio Chela 6-2, 4-6 and 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Krajicek was only playing his first tournament since undergoing
arthroscopic surgery on his left knee in late January, and the
Dutchman improved his career record against Enqvist to 4-3.
</P>
<P>
After the fall of Enqvist, Henman became the 10th seed to fall.
</P>
<P>
Among the big names to fall in the first round were defending
champion Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil and 1997 champion Marcelo Rios
of Chile.
</P>
<P>
The tournament is the first major clay court event in the lead-
up to the Roland Garros and the third in the Masters Series after
Indian Wells and Miami. 
</P>
