<HEADLINE> Company Develops New Handwriting Input System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing-based Jinshan Company
has developed a WPS2000 handwriting input system, which will be
put into the market soon.
</P>
<P>
The software can help users input their handwritings, scripts
and even drawings, according to the Guangming Daily.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the company said that the input technology of the
company follows the principle of "whole sentences and whole
phrases". This enables the computer to recognize more illegible
handwriting.
</P>
<P>
Jinshan Company developed a Chinese-English and English-Chinese
computer dictionary a couple of years ago, which is now widely
used in China. And the handwriting input system will be another
major product of the company.
</P>
<P>
The market potential of the non-keyboard Chinese input is very
big. In Hong Kong, the market share of handwriting input is one-
third of keyboard input, while in the Chinese interior area, the
proportion is one to 100. 
</P>
</TEXT>
