<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Conference on Life Science Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The International Conference on
Life Science and Clinical Medicine 2000, sponsored by the Chinese
Academy of Engineering (CAE), opened in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,200 Chinese experts and medical workers and more
than 80 foreign scholars attended the conference which is co-
hosted by the China Science and Technology Association and 11
other organizations.
</P>
<P>
In the past 100 years, life science has been developing rapidly
and it will greatly affect the development of science, economy and
all of human society in the future, said Zhang Wenkang, minister
of health and the honorary president of the conference.
</P>
<P>
Medical science is an important part of life science, and a
field of application for life science and many other sciences,
said Zhang.
</P>
<P>
Renowned foreign scholars and China's chief scientists in life
science will give speeches on seven subjects including heart and
circulation, cancer, infection, trauma and burns, diabetes and
kidney disease, modernization of traditional medicine, and
environment-toxicology-health.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that the three-day conference will provide a solid
basis for international exchanges in medical science and promote
the development of China's life science and health care.
</P>
<P>
The CAE is the highest honorary and consultative academic
organization for the country's engineering technology circle.
Founded in 1994, the CAE is involved in promoting cooperation
between the scientific and technological circle and cultivate
better personnel in this field.
</P>
<P>
The CAE has also launched various activities for international
academic exchanges and cooperation, and created an open
environment for the progress of the outstanding Chinese young
scientists.  
</P>
</TEXT>
