<BODY>
<HEADLINE> MDMA Sneaks into Chinese Discos (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police have found that
MDMA, a type of amphetamine, has made its way into a number of
Chinese discos, the Ministry of Public Security confirmed today.
</P>
<P>
MDMA is no longer a strange sight to young people in the discos
of Beijing, Shanghai, Nanjing, Guangzhou and Shenzhen, as it was
in 1997 when Chinese police cracked the country's first MDMA case
in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
According to Chen Cunyi, deputy director of the Narcotics
Control Bureau under the Ministry of Public Security, MDMA is an
addictive substance which stimulates the nervous system, causing
drug-users to become easily excited and often to act violently.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that drugs have had a powerfully negative impact
on Chinese society, and the situation has attracted the attention
of both senior government officials and ordinary citizens.
</P>
</TEXT>
