<HEADLINE> Malaysia Welcomes Proposed S. Korea-DPRK Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia welcomes the
proposal to hold a summit between leaders of South Korea and the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) in Pyongynag on June
12-14 this year.
</P>
<P>
"We view the summit as indeed historic in terms of inter-Korean
relations," Malaysian Foreign Minister Syed Hamid Albar said in a
press statement released here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It has been Malaysia's long standing position that differences
between S. Korea and the DPRK be resolved through peaceful
dialogue and that positive measures be taken by both sides in
developing a conducive atmosphere for the establishment of
permanent peace and stability in the Korean Peninsula, the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that peace and stability would not only bring
immense benefits to the two Koreas but to the East Asian region
and the world at large," Syed Hamid said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
