<HEADLINE> Soeharto to Undergo Further Medical Treatment Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Within two days from now on, Mr. Soeharto is due to undergo
further medical treatment to make sure that he is healthy enough
or not to face further questioning," Juan Felix Tampubolon, one of
Soeharto's lawyers told reporters after accompanying Bambang
Trihatmodjo,Soeharto's second son when the latter underwent
investigation as a witness in corruption cases allegedly involved
his father, at the Attorney General Office (AGO).
</P>
<P>
Up till now, the AGO has not collected comprehensive
information from Soeharto to confirm whether the former strong man
has committed abuse of power and piled up fortune illegally during
his 32 years in power.
</P>
<P>
The medical team declared Soeharto is unfit to face
investigation saying the 78-years old man blood pressure arised
surpassing a"tolerable border."
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Trihatmodjo, who was questioned by the AGO for
about 6 hours Wednesday, gave no comments on the investigation
process.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the AGO also summoned Soeharto's eldest daughter
Siti Hardiyanti Indrarukmana for the same cases.
</P>
<P>
The AGO has insisted that it will hammer out to disclose
corruption case allegedly involved the former New Order ruler.
</P>
<P>
It has put the former strong man under city arrest and banned
him from leaving the country. 
</P>
