<HEADLINE> Uganda Receives 39 Million U.S. Dollars for Adjustment Credit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- International Development
Association (IDA) , an arm of the World Bank, has disbursed 58
billion shillings (39 million U.S. dollars) to Uganda for the
second phase of Structural Adjustment Credit (SACII) program.
</P>
<P>
IDA is satisfied with Uganda's progress toward SACII program,
the Monitor daily Wednesday quoted the Bank of Uganda as saying.
</P>
<P>
The first tranche of 66 billion shillings (44 million U.S.
dollars) was disbursed on October 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The money is for development purposes and should be used to
support structural development like schools, roads, modernization
of agriculture and industrialization, said the bank director of
public relations Walugembe Musoke.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the structural adjustment program in Uganda
was effected in 1988 and the second in 1991. 
