<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher in Tokyo on Wall Street Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed higher in Tokyo
Wednesday on continued gains on Wall Street, but the key stock
index failed to regain levels seen last week.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, rose 117.10 points, or 0.62
percent, from Tuesday's close to end at 19,086.62, posting its
first upturn in five trading days.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, surged 23.42 points, or 1.47 percent, to 1,
619.82.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 681.59 million
shares from Tuesday's 749.16 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's rise on Wall Street, combined with the yen's
stabilization at a weak level against the U.S. dollar, led export-
oriented high-tech issues in Tokyo higher, traders said.
</P>
<P>
The planned establishment of several new investment trusts this
week was another factor boosting Tokyo share prices, they said.
</P>
<P>
Information and telecom issues, as well as drugmakers were also
higher,
</P>
<P>
Brokerage houses were the biggest winners, rising 6.57 percent
as a group.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, nonlife insurers, paper manufacturers and air
transportation firms saw declines.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers exceeded
losers 713 to 571, with 104 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
