<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan Sets Key Sectors for Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province will further open some key sectors to encourage foreign
investment in a move to stimulate competition and to assist the
development of west China.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Governor Zhang Zhongwei said the province will open
wider to overseas investment in areas of information technology,
tourism, environment protection, tourism and service in addition
to agriculture development, machinery and electronics, building
materials and decoration industries.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that apart from running joint ventures and solely
foreign-funded enterprises, foreign businessmen can adopt new
approaches for investment such as share-holding, BOT,
incorporating and purchasing, franchises, and issuing bonds abroad.
</P>
<P>
He said that Sichuan has formulated a series of regulations to
encourage foreign enterprises to do business in the province and
to protect their legal rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
The province also set up service centers and a complaint center
for foreign businessmen.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1999 Sichuan had 5,188 foreign-funded enterprises
contracted foreign investment of 13.2 billion U.S. dollars and
actual investment of 6.8 billion U.S. dollars 
</P>
</TEXT>
