<HEADLINE> Belgium-funded Project Launched in Shaanxi Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A project funded by the Belgian
Government aiming to help poverty-stricken people in northwest
China's Shaanxi Province has been launched recently.
</P>
<P>
The project, covering water supply in rural areas, development
concerning women, cultivation of fruit trees and rural sanitation,
will be carried out in three prefectures and cities and six
counties including Jingbian, Zhidan, Yanchuan, Ansai, Wuqi and
Sanyuan in the province.
</P>
<P>
Belgian Government provided 300 million Belgian francs (about 7
million U.S. dollars) and the Chinese side allocated 73.5 million
yuan (8.86 million U.S. dollars) in counterpart funding for the
project, so far the largest joint program regarding helping the
poor between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reached an agreement on the project in February
1999.
</P>
<P>
Andre Sevais, a Belgian representative for the project, visited
Shaanxi recently, saying that the Belgian Government is much
concerned with the project.
</P>
<P>
He said that he will do his best for the implementation of the
project. He expected that the project would enhance exchanges
between Belgium and Shaanxi, and stimulate the social and economic
development in the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
