<HEADLINE> Jinyue Securities Investment Fund Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Six investment funds in east
China's Zhejiang and Jiangsu provinces have merged into an
officially recognized securities investment fund known as Jinyue,
marking further progress made by China in standardizing its
investment funds launched in the early 1990s.
</P>
<P>
The manager of the new fund, the Beijing-based Boshi Fund
Management Company, announced today that the Jinyue fund will be
listed on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange on April 24.
</P>
<P>
After that, the fund will raise its equity from the current 210
million shares to 500 million shares and change its name to Yuhua
Securities Investment Fund.
</P>
<P>
Yuhua will have its validity expanded through December 31, 2007
and will be under the auspices of the Communications Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
The fund will mainly be used to invest in technical stocks.
