<HEADLINE> Nigerian Envoy Delivers Message to Zimbabwean President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Foreign Affairs Minister
Sule Lamido arrived here on Tuesday with a special message for
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe from Nigerian President
Olusegun Obasanjo concerning the dispute between Zimbabwe and
Britain over the land issue.
</P>
<P>
Briefing reporters after meeting with Mugabe, Lamido said the
message is a follow-up to a meeting between Mugabe and British
Foreign Secretary Robin Cook, which was brokered by Obasanjo
during the recent European Union- Africa summit in Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Obasanjo has said he is prepared to mediate in the dispute
between Zimbabwe and Britain over the occupation of white-owned
commercial farms by war veterans.
</P>
<P>
According to the envoy, "President Obasanjo is concerned that
there should be communication between the British government and
the Zimbabwean government... He felt that he will be able to
broker a meeting between the two countries."
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe will soon send a high-powered delegation to London for
talks with the British government on the land issue.
</P>
<P>
President Mugabe has assured Obasanjo, through Lamido, that
apart from "one or two incidents", there was no breakdown in the
rule of law in Zimbabwe and "all is peaceful here", according to
Zimbabwean Deputy Foreign Minister Nicholas Goche. 
</P>
</TEXT>
