</P>
<P>
The Star:
</P>
<P>
-- South African President Thabo Mbeki continued to side-step
the growing crisis in Zimbabwe, in spite of mounting pressure on
the government to break its silence on its troubled northern
neighbor.
</P>
<P>
The Citizen:
</P>
<P>
-- The Johannesburg Stock Exchange bounced back on Tuesday,
recovering many of the losses of Black Monday.
</P>
<P>
Business Day:
</P>
<P>
-- The South African controversial new gun control bill was
being extensively rewritten and Safety and Security Minister Steve
Tshwete had no intention of proceeding with it in its present
form. 
