<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0256 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seed Potato Shortage Looms in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A shortage of seed potato is
looming in Zambia following a recent export ban by South Africa,
said Zambia National Union of Farmers (ZNFU) president Ajay Vashee
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
South African Department of Agriculture slapped a ban on
exports of both potatoes and seed to countries in the region
because of the recent outbreak of potato nematodes disease in that
country, Vashee said in an interview in Ndola in Copperbelt
Province.
</P>
<P>
As a result, there has been no further exports to Zambia
recently, he was quoted by Wednesday's Times of Zambia newspaper
as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Zambia will likely face a serious shortage of both potatoes
and seed in the next few months until the disease in that country
is brought under control," Vashee warned.
</P>
<P>
He commended the move by South Africa as timely because the
disease would otherwise have been imported into Zambia, posing a
serious threat to local potato farmers.
</P>
<P>
Imported crop diseases such as potato nematodes or larger grain
borer for instance, have a serious impact on the local yield which
will require a lot of money to control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
