<HEADLINE> Xi'an Hosts Computer Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Computer Festival for Chinese
University Students is now underway in Xi'an, capital of northwest
China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an is the sixth stop of this nationwide computer promotion
event following Guangzhou, Shanghai, Nanjing, Wuhan, and Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will be held in turn at Xi'an Jiaotong
University, Xi'an University of Science and Engineering, Northwest
University, Northwest China Engineering University, and Xi'an
University of Electronic Science and Technology.
</P>
<P>
The festival opened on March 8 and will run until May 20,
jointly sponsored by the Ministry of Education, the People's Daily,
8 provincial education commissions, and 45 universities.
</P>
<P>
The event displays the newest computer and Internet products,
promotes computer knowledge, and increases the exchanges among
universities in the field of information technology.
</P>
<P>
Many domestic and overseas computer manufactures and Internet
content providers have brought along their latest products.
</P>
<P>
A series of seminars and competitions will be held to provide
college students with more opportunities to keep up with the
latest in computers.
</P>
<P>
After Xi'an, the exhibition will travel to Shenyang, capital of
northeast China's Liaoning Province, and then to the nation's
capital Beijing. 
</P>
