<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Exhibition of Huge Tibetan Painting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A Tibetan painting 618 meters
long and 2.5 meters wide is now being exhibited at the Museum of
Chinese History in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The painting, the longest of its kind in the world, depicts the
history, religion, customs, culture, legends, and daily life of
the Tibetan people, as well as the traditional Tibetan medicine
and architecture in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
It took some 400 artisans four years to complete the work, an
organizer of the exhibition said.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizer, one can see as many as 2,480
separate figures within a 1.3-square-inch area in part of the
painting. 
</P>
