<HEADLINE> Electric Railway Construction In E. China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Work on the electrification of a
186-km-long railway line in east China's Fujian province is
expected to be completed within the year.
</P>
<P>
The project was started late last year, is estimated to cost
990 million yuan (about 108 US dollars), 500 million yuan of which
is from State Development Bank loans.
</P>
<P>
The electrified line links Fuzhou, capital of the province,
with the town of Waiyang, through which the line runs from Xiamen
in Fujian Province to Yingtan in neighboring Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The transportation capacity of the newly electrified line will
be increased greatly, and this is expected to give a big boost to
economic growth in areas through which the line runs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
