<HEADLINE> TCM Production, Trade Center to Be Built in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A center combining research and
development, production and trading of traditional Chinese
medicine (TCM) is scheduled to be built in three to five years in
Jinan, capital of east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has set the goal of having the TCM industry account
for at least five percent of the province's future gross domestic
product.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to establish six state-level bases for
growing herbs used in TCM, and to develop a great variety of TCM
while setting up outlets for their sale.
</P>
<P>
The TCM center will be created in line with modernization and
industrialization, and is expected to play an important role in
increasing the domestic sales and exports of TCM.  
