<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sonics Edge Kings to Avoid Lakers in Playoffs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Gary Payton posted his 10th
career triple doubles to pace the Seattle SuperSonics for a 119-
112 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Tuesday, avoiding a first-
round clash against the Los Angeles Lakers in the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
Payton scored 33 points with 14 assists and 11 rebounds for an
overtime win for the SuperSonics to clinch the seventh seed in the
Western Conference and will face Utah in the first round.
</P>
<P>
Chris Webber had his fifth triple-double of the season with 23
points, 10 rebounds and 13 assists for Sacramento, which went 1-3
against Los Angeles this season.
</P>
<P>
In Cleveland, the Charlotte Hornets scored their sixth straight
victory, a 103-88 edge over the Cavaliers, and will play
Philadelphia in the opening round, beginning Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In Dallas, the league-leading Los Angeles Lakers resorted to
training for substitutes and scored nothing in the fourth quarter
before losing 112-102 to the Mavericks.
</P>
<P>
Shaquille O'Neal had 38 points and 20 rebounds for the Lakers.
</P>
<P>
In Miami, rookie Anthony Carter had 17 points, six assists,
four rebounds as the Heat cruised to a 97-73 rout of the Toronto
Raptors.
</P>
<P>
In Phoenix, the Houston Rockets defeated the Suns 107-98, while
the Atlanta Hawks scored a double overtime win of 111-109 over the
New Jersey Nets.
</P>
<P>
In Chicago, the Philadelphia 76ers edged the Bulls 93-89
despite Allen Iverson was on the injuried list.
</P>
<P>
In Denver, Raef LaFrentz scored a career-high 32 points and
blocked six shots as the Nuggets managed a 105-104 victory over
the Utah Jazz.
</P>
<P>
In New York, Allan Houston scored 29 points to leading the
Knicks to a 100-88 victory over Detroit.
</P>
<P>
In Washington, the Boston Celtics won a lackluster 114-81
victory over the Wizards and the Portland Trail Blazers dealt a
116-100 loss to the Los Angeles Clippers, their 17th in a row.
</P>
</TEXT>
