<HEADLINE> Software Companies Alliance Going on In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The forming of a nationwide
alliance of companies involved in software development and
production, as well as software system integration and services is
underway in China.
</P>
<P>
The project was launched by NEU-Alpine, a leading Chinese
software firm based in Shenyang, capital of northeast China's
Liaoning Province, aiming at building a powerful information
technology (IT) coalition by inviting the participation of
software businesses across the country.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the "All Win Alliance" is expected to make
better use of technology, management, operation and marketing
advantages of individual firms, in a bid to further promote the
development of the country's software industry.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 big domestic and overseas software companies have
decided to join in the alliance. 
</P>
