<HEADLINE> Inflow of Overseas Investment Rising In Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Shandong Province, one of China's
leading economic generators, registered 920 million US dollars of
contractual overseas investment during the first quarter of the
year, a leap of 45 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The increase is 17 percentage points higher than the national
growth average.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-five of the newly established overseas-funded
enterprises during the quarter each absorbed more than 10 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao led all the cities in the province with 500 million US
dollars of contractual overseas fund during the three-month period,
up 45 percent on 1999 figure.
</P>
<P>
Inflow of investment from the U.S., the ROK and Germany showed
a big rise. And local projects in machinery, electronics,
pharmaceuticals and infrastructure construction still remain
attractive for overseas investors. 
</P>
