<HEADLINE> Taiwan Firm to Increase Investment in Chinese Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Renowned Taiwan electronics and
plastics giant Grace T.H.W. Group plans to double its investment
in the Chinese mainland over the next few years.
</P>
<P>
This announcement was made by Winston Wong, chairman of the
board of the group, at a ceremony held in Shanghai earlier this
week marking the opening of the Shanghai Grace Fabric Company. The
new company was jointly established by the group and two companies
in Shanghai at cost of 74.5 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
