<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Legal Expert Urges Patent Protection for Traditional Chinese Medicine (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Because existing intellectual
property protection measures fail to protect traditional Chinese
medicine, one legal expert suggested today that China should find
new ways to protect these products.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturers should be allowed to patent effective ingredients
and prescriptions, according to Wang Bing, professor at the Law
School of Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
Judicial bodies should check technical characteristics for the
purpose of identifying any possible infringement, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
According to theories of Chinese medicine, effective
ingredients are a class of compounds used in various Chinese
medicine prescriptions.
</P>
<P>
 The most effective method to protect these compounds is for
enterprises to file patent applications for the chemical
components, the law professor said.
</P>
<P>
"But it is not possible to do this based on current
technologies," he said.
</P>
<P>
"As with other medicines, Chinese medicine is the result of
human intelligence and has commercial value," he said, "therefore,
it is also a kind of intellectual property and should be protected
by law."
</P>
<P>
For thousands of years, Chinese people contributed their
intelligence to Chinese medicine and have left more than 100,000
traditional prescriptions.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Legal Expert Urges Patent Protection for Traditional Chinese Medicine (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"It is difficult for the present legislation to fully protect
the intellectual property rights of Chinese medicine since the
intellectual property protection system was set up far later than
the development of Chinese medicine," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, there are many cases in which the intellectual
property rights of Chinese medicine are infringed, but nothing can
be done by legislation, he said.
</P>
<P>
"A new kind of medicine might be quickly produced by an
enterprise which is not the legal owner of the medicine after it
is developed," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
In this case, the enterprise which develops the medicine
obtains no reasonable returns, and this limits the overall
development of Chinese medicine, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Patent Law issued in 1985 protects the process of medicine
manufacturing rather than its chemical substances.
</P>
<P>
As foreigners understand more and more about the negative
effects of Western medicine, development of new medicines from
natural plants, particularly from traditional Chinese medicine,
has became quite popular.
</P>
<P>
Some companies in developed countries rampantly copy Chinese
medicine, causing China to lose its intellectual property rights
in this field, Wang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Armed Police Speed up Modernization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China's People's Armed Police
Force has speeded up the upgrading of its command, monitoring,
maintenance, and other related systems with advanced
telecommunications and Internet technology.
</P>
<P>
Today's Liberation Army Daily reports that most of the armed
police corps in provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions
have created comprehensive combat command systems integrating the
use of computers and telecommunications technology.
</P>
<P>
The upgraded command systems can enhance communications between
tens of thousands of duty posts nationwide, and among armed police
corps in municipalities and provinces with their Beijing-based
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The global positioning system and the mobile-based microwave
televised reconnaissance system also provide reliable resources
for command personnel.
</P>
<P>
Modernized devices helped to safely solve more than 10
kidnapping cases last year, the daily said.
</P>
<P>
Advanced armored carriers, multi-functional refueling trucks,
field water-supply vehicles, and other kinds of equipment have
also helped enhance the combat capability of the armed police.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that now the armed police's capacity to deal
with unexpected events while fulfilling their regular duties has
been greatly improved.  
</P>
</TEXT>
