<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0285 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Tea Export Target Not to Be Met </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's export target for tea
in the current fiscal year will not be fulfilled, the Financial
Express reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The reasons given for the expected failure in fulfilling of the
export target included the falls in tea production and quality
this year, the plummeting of tea price in the international market,
and the increase of local consumption of tea due to the
urbanization process.
</P>
<P>
According to information obtained from the Export Promotion
Bureau(EPB), the export target for tea was set at 40 million U.S.
dollars.During the first eight months of the current fiscal (July
1900-February 2000), 8.48 million kilograms of tea valued at 12.19
million dollars were exported.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the EPB held the view that it is impossible to
reach the export target during the remaining four months (March-
June) of the current year.
</P>
<P>
During the July-February period last fiscal, 19.24 million
kilograms of tea valued at 33.10 million dollars were exported.
The export target for July-February period of the current fiscal
was set at 26.67 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
