<HEADLINE> European MPs to Visit Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- An 18-member delegation led by
Chairman of the European Parliament is arriving here on April 20
on a three-day friendly visit to Nepal, Radio Nepal reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the delegation will include Gerard
Collins, the chairman of the parliament, and members of parliament
of seven countries -- Ireland, France, Germany, Spain, Britain,
the Netherlands and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The European MPs' visit to Nepal is aimed at strengthen the
ties of Europe with Nepal and promoting democracy in the Himalayan
kingdom, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will meet separately with Prime Minister G.P.
Koirala, Speaker of the House of Representatives Taranath Ranabhat,
National Assembly Chairman Mohammad Moshin, Minister for Foreign
Affairs Chakra Bastola and Minister for Finance Mahesh Acharya.
</P>
<P>
The delegates and the members of the Foreign Affairs and Human
Rights Committees of the Nepali House of Representatives are
scheduled to exchange views on parliamentary exercise and
activities.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will also visit the SAARC (South Asia
Association for Regional Cooperation) Secretariat based here and
the Bhutanese refugee camps in eastern Nepal.
</P>
<P>
About 100,000 Bhutanese refugees are living in seven refugee
camps managed by the United Nations since they were evicted from
their country in the 1990's. 
</P>
