<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cowens Named Head Coach for Warriors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Dave Cowens was named head
coach for the Golden State Warriors on Tuesday, becoming the 19th
coach in Warriors franchise history.
</P>
<P>
Once the coach of the Charlotte Hornets, Cowens joined Golden
State's staff on January 31, but the Warriors are without the
playoff berth for the sixth straight year. They are 19-62 and
have the third-worst record in the NBA.
</P>
<P>
However, the Warriors acquired second-year guard Larry Hughes
in February who can pair with forward Antawn Jamison next season.
Jamison was leading the team in scoring before suffering a season-
ending knee injury just before Hughes' arrival.
</P>
<P>
Cowens, 51, guided Charlotte to a 109-70 (.609) record in 179
games but resigned March 8, 1999 after the Hornets opened the
lockout-abbreviated season with just four wins in their first 15
games.
</P>
<P>
Voted one of the NBA's 50 Greatest Players, Cowens had a
stellar career primarily with the Boston Celtics. He served as
player-coach for 68 games during the 1978-79 season.
</P>
<P>
Cowens also served as an assistant on the San Antonio Spurs'
staff. His career coaching record is 136-111 (.551). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
