<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Finnish Old Man Dead for 6 Years Before Discovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI,April 18 (Xinhua) -- An old man was found dead alone
in a Helsinki apartment last week and police said he died six
years ago, press reports here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Police found a mummy inside an apartment in Maunula district
last Friday after they were called in by maintenance men who had
been trying to install fire alarms for the apartment but got no
one to answer the door and smelt a strange odor from inside.
</P>
<P>
From the dates of the ads scattered in the room, the police
identified the deceased as a retiree who died six years ago at 55.
</P>
<P>
The man was said to have children who were living in the same
city, and used to get on well with his neighbors. For the past six
years, social welfare authorities transferred monthly retirement
pensions to his banking account and the social affairs department
under the municipality collected rent from his account each month.
</P>
<P>
Many people, particularly those living in the capital, were
shocked at the news.
</P>
<P>
The Finnish TV commented Tuesday that the event was a mockery
to a nation enjoying sophisticated information technology, a
tragedy for the developed welfare society, and an exposure of the
extent of bureaucracy.
</P>
<P>
It constituted a breach of duty on the part of the social
administration, Basic Services Minister Osmo Soininvaara said.
</P>
<P>
To avoid similar tragedies in the future, the social affairs
administration under the Helsinki municipality decided Tuesday to
modify relevant ordinances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
