<HEADLINE> Precipitation Forecast for Parts of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Most areas of northern China and
parts of southern China are expected to see rain from Wednesday to
Friday this week, according to China's Central Meteorological
Observatory today.
</P>
<P>
The observatory said rainfall or snowfall ranging from two to
10 mm is forecast for the southeast part of northwest China, most
parts of north China, northeast China, and areas between the
Yellow and Huaihe rivers.
</P>
<P>
It said the rainfall is expected to be 15 to 30 mm for the
eastern part of both the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region and
Hebei Province, and most parts of northeast China.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, precipitation ranging three to 20 mm
is expected for the eastern part of the Sichuan Basin, the Hanshui
River Basin, and most parts of the regions including the Yangtze
River- Huaihe River areas and the Yangtze River - Nanling
Mountains areas, and south China.
</P>
<P>
The rainfall may be 30 to 50 mm for some of the regions, and 60
to 80 mm for a few isolated areas, with occasional rainstorms and
strong wind.
</P>
<P>
Most part of China are forecast to have fresh breezes to
moderate gales, while the Bohai Bay, the Yellow Sea, the East
China Sea, and the Taiwan Straits and the northeast part of the
South China Sea are expected to see fresh breezes to moderate
gales.  
</P>
</TEXT>
