<HEADLINE> Myanmar Criticizes U.S.'s Human Rights Accusations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Official newspaper The New Light
of Myanmar Wednesday criticized the United States for its
continuous accusations of other countries on human rights.
</P>
<P>
"America, while ignoring human rights violation at home and
peaceful and developed situations of other countries, is firing
air bullets of accusations continuously," said the newspaper in an
article.
</P>
<P>
The U.S.' state and labor departments issue slanderous
accusations on other countries year after year, but no country
ever accepts its accusations but responds and rejects with anger,
the article said.
</P>
<P>
"Over five million poor people and seven million homeless in
America are losing human rights due to the wide gap between the
rich and the poor, racial discrimination and status discrimination,
" the article said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Myanmar government rejected last month a report
on labor practices in the country for 2000 issued by the U.S.
Labor Department, saying that the report is full of false and
malicious allegations.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Myanmar also refuted a report on the human rights
situation of countries in the world issued by the U.S. State
Department, accusing it of taking a prejudiced stance toward this
country with politically motivated attempts to meddle in its
internal affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
