<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Modernize Coast Tourism Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan National Tourist
Board has launched a survey of infrastructure facilities available
on the southwest coast to modernize at least eight tourist resorts
in the area, the official Daily News reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the study, which is funded by the United Nations
Development Program, is to draw up an environmentally acceptable
and economically viable 10-year infrastructure improvement plan
and identify opportunities for private sector tourism development.
</P>
<P>
A key element of the study will be the improvement of the
environmental conditions and promotion of environmental awareness
programs within the local communities, said the report, adding
that the improvement plan is expected to be completed by the end
of this year.
</P>
<P>
Last year Sri Lanka recorded an all time high tourist arrival
figure of more than 436,400 which is an increase of 14.5 percent
over the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
