<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 128 On Board Ill-fated Air Philippines Plane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Defense Secretary
Orlando Mercado confirmed reports that an Air Philippines with 128
passengers and crew members on board crashed Wednesday morning in
the southern province of Davao del Norte.
</P>
<P>
Reports said 122 passengers, including 4 children, and 6 crew
members were on board flight 541 when the Davao bound plane went
down.
</P>
<P>
Rescue teams have reached the crash site but no body or
survivor has been found as of press time.
</P>
<P>
The Boeing 737-200 was reported missing at around 07:05 (23:05
GMT,Tuesday) in Mount Camanlangan, Sitio San Isidro Samal Island
by the Air Transportation Office of Davao.
</P>
<P>
The Flight 541 left the Philippine capital of Manila at around
05:20(21:20 GMT, Tuesday) and was expected to reach Davao City at
06:45(22:45 GMT, Tuesday).
</P>
<P>
Initial reports said the pilot of the plane reported zero
visibility before the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
