<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Foreign trade in east China's Anhui
Province was reported to rise 47.8 percent year-on-year to 770
million US dollars during the first quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
Imports went up 55.5 percent to 311 million US dollars and
exports grew by 42.9 percent to 459 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
