conducted by means of general trade, which accounts for an
increasing part of local foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The province's exports to Asia are growing and reached 220
million US dollars during the period, due to the economic recovery
in some Asia's countries which were once plagued by financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Local state-owned enterprises handled 528 million US dollars of
foreign trade during the three-month period, accounting for 68.6
percent of the local total. 
