<HEADLINE> Mexicans Protest Emigrant Deaths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 18 (Xinhua)-- Mexicans held a 110-kilometer
march near the U.S. border areas Tuesday to protest the death of
their compatriots who tried to enter the U.S. territory.
</P>
<P>
The protest, called "Emigrant's Way of the Cross", began in
Tijuana city, southern Mexico, bordering the United States, and
will end in Mexican area called La Rumorosa Friday.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the march said that a total of 502 people have
died when they tried to enter the American side illegally since
the U.S. government implemented "Operation Guardian" in the
Mexican-U.S. border area in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The operation for greater border vigilance has forced emigrants
to use more dangerous ways, and as a result some of them died from
dehydration, cold or isolation.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the protesters said he hopes the U.S. and
Mexican governments will make more flexible migration policies to
prevent further deaths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
