<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0327 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Company Builds New Chip Against Hacker Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A Silicon Valley-based
company has built a new chip for its networking equipment that can
prevent intruders from attacking Web sites.
</P>
<P>
Juniper Networks, a leading provider of next-generation
Internet protocol infrastructure systems, said Tuesday that it is
shipping the new processor that can scan all the data flowing
through a network without slowing down the traffic.
</P>
<P>
The company called it a breakthrough in application specific
integrated circuit (ASIC), designed to integrate a large number of
functions in one chip so as to boost data handling to the speed
and capacity of optical pipes.
</P>
<P>
The new chip, called Internet Processor II, could prevent the
hacker attacks that crippled many of the top Web sites in February,
according to the company.
</P>
<P>
The security feature was available in software in the past, but
it slowed down networks so much that Internet service providers
and telecommunications carriers only used it sparingly, Juniper
said. The new chip can filter 20 million packets of data per
second, while security software in the past could only scan 200,
000 packets of data per second.
</P>
<P>
The Internet Processor II has over 2.5 million gates, twice the
size of, and offering far richer capabilities than, Internet
Processor, the first-generation ASIC introduced in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Juniper said that the new processor will allow service
providers to offer new services to customers. Because the chip can
view the packets of Net information, it allows service providers
to give higher priority to more important data. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0328 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Royal Canadian Mint Issues New Coin Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Royal Canadian Mint Tuesday
launched its new series of 20-Canadian dollar (about 13.46 U.S.
dollars) coins featuring the country's achievements in
transportation.
</P>
<P>
The three sterling silver hologram cameo coins each contains
one troy ounce of sterling silver (92.5 percent silver, 7.5
percent copper) and bears a 24 karat gold-plated holographic cameo.
</P>
<P>
Mintage of each individual coin is limited to 15,000 worldwide,
said the country's Crown corporation.
</P>
<P>
Early in the day, the corporation issued its 2000 50-cent
sterling silver coin series of birds of prey. It also issued the
eleventh and twelfth coins to complete its three-year sterling
silver fifty-cent sports series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
