<HEADLINE> Xiamen Introduces More Investment from Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen, a coastal city in east
China's Fujian Province, approved 26 new Taiwan-funded enterprises
in the first quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
The projects involve 22.36 million US dollars of contractual
investment from Taiwan, a 1.7 times increase from 1999.
</P>
<P>
Local Taiwan-funded enterprises are mostly involved in
manufacturing and mainly 100-percent owned by Taiwan investors.
</P>
<P>
During the first quarter of the year, six Taiwan-funded
enterprises added 14.15 million US dollars of investment in
expanding production in Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
By the end of March, 1,690 Taiwan-funded projects were approved
in Xiamen, involving 3 billion US dollars of contractual
investment from Taiwan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
