<HEADLINE> Luxury Cruise Ship Between China and Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A luxury ship equipped with first
class hotel facilities will start its first trip from China's
southernmost island province of Hainan to Vietnam in June.
</P>
<P>
The navigation route jointly operated by Hainan and the Star
Cruises (Hong Kong) Co. Ltd will become officially operational on
October 1, China's National Day.
</P>
<P>
"Baopingxing" Ship can accommodate 1,900 passengers and will
make three trips a week. Each trip will take 36 hours.
</P>
<P>
The cruise ship will stop over in Haikou, capital of Hainan,
Sanya and Ha Long and Hai-phong in Vietnam. 
