<HEADLINE> Domestic Investment Increases in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The number of companies set up
in Shanghai by investors from other parts of China reached 221
during the first quarter of the year, involving 2.3 billion yuan
in registered capital.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises include 157 involved in manufacturing, trade,
catering and social services. Thirty-six of these enterprises are
backed by private investors.
</P>
<P>
Neighboring Zhejiang Province ranks first in funding 37
enterprises in Shanghai, followed by Jiangsu Province with 36
companies and Beijing with 33 firms.
</P>
<P>
In terms of registered capital, Shenzhen took the lead with 540
million yuan, followed by Zhejiang province with 460 million yuan.
