<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Lists 163 Key Projects for Year 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province plans to
launch 163 key projects this year, which are estimated to cost 58
billion yuan, with 13.4 billion yuan to be invested this year.
</P>
<P>
The projects are mainly involved in capital construction,
technological upgrading, agricultural and social development. Some
48.6 billion yuan will be used in infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang is currently building five expressways and will
further upgrade electric grids in rural areas, and speed up
construction of a power station and seabed cable trunks in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The province will also upgrade its industries, developing high-
efficiency agriculture and higher education.
</P>
<P>
Local GDP is expected to rise by 9 percent this year compared
with the 1999 figure, with investment in fixed assets to grow by
10 percent. 
