<HEADLINE> Hainan's Yangpu Development Zone Ready for Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Yangpu Economic Development Zone
in south China's Hainan Province is now ready to usher in a new
stage of overseas investment, according to a local economic
official.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Xuancheng, director of the zone, said during a news
briefing on latest development of investment environment and new
policies of the state-level zone, that the zone will be turned
into an export-oriented industrial area dominated by processing
industries.
</P>
<P>
Set up in 1992 with the approval of the State Council, Yangpu
Economic Development Zone covers an area of 31 sq. km and is one
of the country's 32 state-level economic development zones where
diversified preferential policies are offered. A total of 5.3
billion yuan was spent building infrastructure systems, including
transportation, power supply and telecommunications facilities.
</P>
<P>
Construction is underway on a number of major industrial
projects involving a total investment of ten billion yuan. The
projects include a pulp plant, an optical fiber cable firm and a
soy grease company.  
