- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus Foreign Minister Ioannis Kasoulides said here
Tuesday that the Cyprus government aims to find a just and viable
solution to the Cyprus issue and to work for accession to the
European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 17th meeting of the EU-Cyprus Joint
Parliamentary Committee, Kasoulides reiterated that the two
objectives are two parallel courses "which aim at strengthening
each other". (Cyprus-Two Goals)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Several guerrilla rockets hit settlements in
northern Israel along the border with Lebanon, but no casualties
were reported yet, Israel Defense Forces officers said Tuesday
evening.
</P>
<P>
At least 30 Russian-made Katyusha rockets were fired by
Lebanese Hezbollah guerrillas, who have been fighting to end
Israeli occupation in south Lebanon since early 1980s, but only
three or four of them landed at the entrance to two Jewish
settlements in western Galilee, the officers in Jerusalem revealed.
(Israel-Lebanon-Hezbollah)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON-- British Prime Minister Tony Blair is visiting Northern
Ireland Tuesday in an attempt to breathe new life into the
deadlocked peace process.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials from British and Irish governments have been
trying to work out a formula which would allow the re-
establishment of the political institutions in Northern Ireland.
(Britain-N.Ireland)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HARARE -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe said Tuesday that
his government was determined to resolve the land issue once and
for all.
</P>
<P>
In his national address to mark 20 years of independence,
Mugabe said the issue of land was the last colonial question
heavily qualifying the sovereignty of the people of Zimbabwe. (
Zimbabwe-President)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's outgoing conservative Majlis or parliament
Tuesday passed a hard-line amendment to the press law, imposing
more restrictions on the country's freedom-seeking press.
</P>
<P>
The newly-approved amendment sets more strict conditions for
authorities to grant licenses to publications and instructs the
Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance to investigate any
complaints against the press. (Iran-Press Law)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- A leading pediatrician who is advising the
federal government on the Elian Gonzalez case Tuesday urged the
government to take immediate measures to rescue the boy, saying
that the boy is being psychologically abused by his Miami
relatives.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the National Broadcasting Company (NBC) TV show, Dr.
Irwin Redlener said a home video about Elian released by the
relatives last week looks "exactly like we might see in a hostage
situation." (US-Cuban Boy) 
</P>
