<HEADLINE> Barcelona Reach Last Four of Euro Champions Leauge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Barcelona of Spain reached the
last four of the European Champions League soccer tournament after
beating Chelsea of England 5-1 after extra time in Barcelona on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona, who lost 3-1 in their first leg encounter, advanced
with a 6-4 aggregate, setting up an all-Spanish semifinal against
Valencia for a place in the May 24 final in Paris.
</P>
<P>
After Barcelona had moved effectively ahead with first half
goals by Rivaldo and Luis Figo, Tore Andre Flo replied for
Gianluca Vialli's Blues after a blunder by goalkeeper Ruud Hesp.
</P>
<P>
Substitute Dani headed Barcelona's third but Rivaldo missed a
penalty five minutes from the end of regular time and the game
went into an extra 30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Then Rivaldo converted his second penalty attempt and Patrick
Kluivert headed the fifth as Barcelona charged into the last four.
</P>
