<HEADLINE> Maccabi Tel Aviv to Meet Panathinaikos in Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Nathan Huffman scored 24 points as
Maccabi Tel Aviv beat Barcelona 65-51 in the semifinal of the
basketball Euro Final Four in Thessaloniki, Greece.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli team will play in Thursday's final against
Panathinaikos Athens, which got 22 points from Yugoslav guard
Dejan Bodiroga in an 81-71 win over Istanbul's Efes Pilsen.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona, which has played in five finals since 1984 but has
never won a championship, will play Efes Pilsen for third place
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
American guard Anthony Goldwire, who played in the National
Basketball Association for the Charlotte Hornets and Denver
Nuggets, led Barcelona with 13 points.
</P>
<P>
After struggling in the game's opening minutes, Maccabi took
control, and opened up a 38-22 lead at halftime.
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal, Panathinaikos took the lead in the
first two minutes of its game and never looked back.
</P>
<P>
Playing a controlled passing game, the Athens squad lead by as
many as 12 points in the first half and 18 in the second.
</P>
<P>
Efes, which tried to implement a tight zone defense, got as
close as seven points with less than three minutes to play.
</P>
</TEXT>
