<HEADLINE> Income Tax Revenue Rising in Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen, one of China's five
special economic zones, collected 149.25 million yuan in personal
income taxes in the coastal city of east China's Fujian Province
during the first quarter of the year, a 20.21 percent rise year-on-
year.
</P>
<P>
The increase is due to the high-speed growth in local exports.
</P>
<P>
