<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Better Conditions For Soldiers Guarding S. China Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Living conditions and logistic
supplies for Chinese soldiers guarding Nansha Islands in South
China Sea have been greatly improved in recent years, according to
sources from the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
Helicopters have become a major means of transport, while
concrete-made fortifications have replaced outdated, shabby huts.
Helicopter pads have been built on several big islands.
</P>
<P>
In addition to modern weaponry and reconnaissance equipment,
troops are now equipped with dish antennas, high-efficient
refrigerators, Karaoke equipment and VCDs. A newly-built drinking
water storage is capable of meeting the needs for several months.
</P>
<P>
All the officers in the troops are university or college
graduates, including some with master or doctorate degrees.
</P>
</TEXT>
