<DOCNO> XIE20000419.0364 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran, Yemen Ink Agreements on Joint Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Iran and Yemen on Wednesday signed
three agreements on cooperation in the fields of politics, air
transportation and fisheries, the Islamic Republic News Agency
(IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The documents, signed here in the presence of Iranian President
Mohammed Khatami and his visiting Yemeni counterpart Ali Abdullah
Saleh, will pave the way for further expansion of ties between the
two Muslim countries, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi and his Yemeni
counterpart Abdul Qader Bajammal signed a letter of understanding
on bilateral political cooperation, stressing the need for
enhancing cooperation between the foreign ministries of Iran and
Yemen in various fields.
</P>
<P>
A second agreement, signed by the transportation ministers of
the two countries, calls for the running of punctual air services
between the air spaces of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
A letter of understanding on cooperation in the field of
fisheries, signed by the Iranian construction minister and the
Yemeni fisheries minister, authorizes Iran to embark on fishing
endeavors in Yemeni waters as well as the dispatch of three Iranian
ships to help Yemen assess its reserves of maritime resources.
</P>
<P>
Yemeni President Saleh, with a 90-member delegation of ministers
and other officials, is to leave here on Wednesday at the end of a
three-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Saleh held talks with President Khatami and
Iranian supreme leader Seyyed Ali Husseini Khamenei. Both sides
stressed the importance of close cooperation in maintaining
security and stability in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
