<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100GMT, Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi Vice President Taha Yassin Ramadan has stressed
that Iraq will never implement the U.N. Security Council Resolution
1284 because it fails to respond to Iraq's demand for a total
lifting of the decade-old sanctions.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. resolution, as a product of the British colonialist
mentality designed to put Iraq under its mandate, transferred Iraq
from conditional sanctions to everlasting embargo, Ramadan was
quoted as saying by the Iraqi News Agency (INA) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Iraq does not pin hope on the U.N. Security Council to lift the
sanctions, but will let the embargo get eroded by itself, said
Ramadan. (Iraq-UN-Resolution)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel held a grand
ceremony at the Presidential Palace Wednesday morning to welcome
Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Upon their arrival at the presidential Palace, President Jiang
and his wife Wang Yeping were warmly greeted by Demirel and his
wife Nazniye.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Demirel mounted to the reviewing stand amid a salvo
of 21 guns. The national anthems of China and Turkey were played.
Accompanied by Demirel, Jiang inspected a guard of honor greeting
them in Turkish "Merhaba Asker." (Turkey-China-Jiang)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here Wednesday that
China would like to promote overall ties with Turkey by forging a
new cooperative partnership with Turkey based on the principles of
mutual respect and trust, equality and mutual benefit, common
development and long-term stability.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during his talks with Turkish President
Suleyman Demirel. (Turkey-China-Ties)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- The Palestinian students of Damascus University held
a silent sit-in in front of the United Nations office here on
Wednesday on the occasion of the "Palestinian Captive Day."
</P>
<P>
The sit-in was called by the Palestinian Student Federation
(PSF) and the Committee on Defense of Palestinian Detainees in
Israeli Jails (CDPD).
</P>
<P>
The protesters handed over two memos, from the PSF and CDPD to
U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan, to the residing representative
of the U.N. Development Program in Damascus Tawfiq Bin Emara.
</P>
<P>
The two memos condemned the "atrocious and inhumane" treatment
practised by the Israeli occupation authorities against Palestinian
detainees. (Syria-Palestinian Students-Sit-in)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang Zemin delivered a
speech here on Wednesday on the Sino-Turkish relations, the
international situation, domestic affairs and other issues at a
banquet held in his honour by his Turkish counterpart Suleyman
Demirel. (Turkey-Chinese President Speech)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel said here Wednesday
that the ongoing visit to Turkey by Chinese President Jiang Zemin
has not only brought the traditional friendship of the Chinese
people to the country, but furthered the bilateral friendly ties
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a banquet he hosted in honour of the Chinese
president, Demirel called the visit a "historic" one which will
guarantee the prospect of the bilateral ties. (Turkey-Demirel-
Jiang) 
</P>
