<HEADLINE> Chile Rejects Nazism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Chile's famous political and
social personalities, along with the local Jewish community
leaders,on Wednesday called for a rejection of Nazism via a
signature gathering meeting.
</P>
<P>
The initiative is aimed to "join the country against Nazi
ideology, which through history has shown itself against the
highest human ideals," they said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Among the members organizing this event are Andres Zaldivar,
President of the Senate, Francisco Lopez, National Director of the
National Youth Institute, and the leaders of the Democratic Jewish
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of signatures have been gathered so far.
</P>
<P>
On April 11, the Chilean government prohibited the entry into
Chilean territory of Nazis coming from abroad to stay in the
country for a Nazi congress from April 17 to 22.
</P>
<P>
The authorities have adopted measures to stop the organizer of
the Nazi congress, Alexis Lopez, and to follow the traces of the
probable place where the event would take place.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of young people marched in protest in Santiago's main
streets and delivered to the authorities a box with over 15,000
signed letters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
