<HEADLINE> Romania Salutes Russia's Ratification of Start II Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Romania salutes the
ratification of the Start II Treaty by the Russian Federation and
expresses the hope that the coming into force of this treaty will
accelerate the process of reduction of nuclear weapons, opening
the way to Start III, spokeswoman for the Romanian Foreign
Ministry Ireny Comaroschi told a Wednesday's briefing.
</P>
<P>
The ratification of the Start II Treaty demonstrates the
political will of the Russian Federation to scale down nuclear
weaponry and to continue, in this way, the disarmament process, in
conformity with article 6 of the treaty for non-proliferation of
nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
An event waited for a long time, the ratification of Start II
will have beneficial effects on the work of the conference of
evaluation of the applying of the treaty for non-proliferation of
nuclear weapons and, on a larger plane, in the unblocking of the
negotiations regarding the treaty for cutting off the production
of fission materials for military purposes, the encouraging of the
strategic nuclear stability, in tension zones in the first place,
such as South Asia, added the spokeswoman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
