<HEADLINE> Reno Says "Mafiaboy" Hacker Must Be Punished </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 19 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Attorney General Janet
Reno said Wednesday a 15-year-old boy arrested in Canada for
attacking the CNN Website in February must face punishment.
</P>
<P>
The FBI and prosecutors from the Computer Crimes Section have
been working with investigators from the Royal Canadian Mounted
Police, and the joint efforts resulted in the arrest of a 15-year-
old suspect, by the Canadian police in Montreal Saturday morning,
Reno told reporters on Capitol Hill.
</P>
<P>
The suspect, who goes by the online name Mafiaboy, has been
charged in connection with the cyberattack on the CNN Network
website.
</P>
<P>
"There has got to be a remedy, there has got to be a penalty,"
Reno said.
</P>
<P>
The attorney general said that it is important to let young
people know that they are not going to be able to get away with
something like this because of age.
</P>
<P>
"But more importantly, we have got to renew our efforts to
teach young people cyberethics so that we ensure that this tool is
used by all concerned to expand our opportunity for learning, for
communications, for commerce," she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
