<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Fall From Strong Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks fell
Wednesday as investors took profits from a strong rebound in the
previous two sessions.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 92.46 at 10,674.96.
The index rose 461.65 points in total Tuesday and Monday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly lower. The technology
heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 87.16 at 3,706.41, trimming its
big gain of 472.28 points in the previous two-day rally.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index fell 14.14 at 1,427.47.
</P>
<P>
The stocks plunged as investor took some money out of the
market to lock in profits the two-day rally. They were in a
sentiment that the rally may be overdone, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Intel dropped Wednesday after a previous sharp rise and IBM
also fell, dragging the Dow index. But Qualcomm, the maker of
mobile phone technology, rose amid a strong earnings report.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE fell 1.54 at 633.27. But the American Stock Exchange
index rose 8.87 at 886.23 and the Russell 2000 index of smaller
companies rose 0.15 at 486.23.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a narrow margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,491 down, 1,479 up and 469
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 996.46 million shares from 1.09 billion
in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
